 "market_recap": "Semis ripped on June 9 on the memory supercycle. Micron's capex boost and Bank of America's raised equipment estimates lifted MU up 9.9%, AMAT up 8.6%, KLAC up 9.3% and LRCX up 7%, while Marvell jumped 9.6% on S&P 500 inclusion plus Jensen Huang calling it the next trillion-dollar name. Underneath that, a tech de-risking dragged the Nasdaq down about 1% (S&P 500 down 0.3%) ahead of CPI: quantum (IONQ down 9.7% as Quantinuum's blockbuster debut reset valuations), optical (LITE down 8.2% on profit-taking), and rare earth (MP down 5.7% as US-China tension eased) all gave back gains.",
 "macro_context": "May CPI, out 8:30 ET this morning, ran hot on the headline at 4.2% year over year, the highest since April 2023, but core was the relief: 0.2% month over month (below the 0.3% feared) and 2.9% year over year. Energy drove more than 60% of the monthly increase, tied to the Iran war and Strait of Hormuz disruption, so the inflation is being read as an energy shock rather than broad demand. Markets still expect the Fed on hold at the June 17 meeting. Watch PPI Thursday and the SpaceX mega-IPO Friday.",
